<23 Apr>

*FLOW CONTROL*

<shortcut>
1. main-> cnt+space+enter
2.syso. -> cnt+space bar 
3.to get options in eclipse press control +1
4.to formate the code in eclipse press control+shift+F 
5. comment control+forward /

Rule 1:
Start execution from main() method of program 

Rule 2:
When cursor goes to method calling statement runs then it transfer the control to matching method;

Rule 3:
closing bracket of user define method runs then control comes back to calling statement


Rule 4:
when closing bracket of main() method runs complete stops  

Example:

public class MyClass {
    public static void main(String args[]) { //Rule 1
     A.a1=new A(); //NO
     a1.test();//Rule 2
     
    }//Rule 4
    
    void test() //from Rule 2
    {
       System.out.println(1000); 
    }
}

*No of Arguments*

The main purpose of method is to reuse and makes program well structured. 

++++++++++++++++

a1.test(100,200,300,400);

public void test(int...i) //can store any argument 
{
	sop(i[0]);
	sop(i[1]);
	sop(i[2]);
	sop(i[3]);

}

+++++++++++++

*Var data type cannot be used for method arguments.

a1.test(100,"abby",30.40);

public void test(var...i) //Error.
{
	sop(i[0]);
	sop(i[1]);
	sop(i[2]);
	sop(i[3]);

}


